      <h2>Intelligent Building Energy Management</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial buildings consume energy across multiple systems — lighting, HVAC, hot water, refrigeration, and plug loads. Without centralised management, each system operates independently, leading to waste and missed efficiency gains.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our building automation systems connect solar, battery, heat pump, and conditioning systems into a single managed platform. The result is coordinated control that reduces energy consumption and operating costs.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Automate</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Solar and battery management</strong> — optimise self-consumption, peak shaving, and export</li>
        <li><strong>HVAC scheduling</strong> — condition spaces only when occupied, pre-cool or pre-heat using solar energy</li>
        <li><strong>Demand response</strong> — automatically reduce load during peak pricing or grid events</li>
        <li><strong>Monitoring and reporting</strong> — real-time dashboards and historical data for energy auditing and sustainability reporting</li>
        <li><strong>Fault detection</strong> — early warning when systems underperform or deviate from expected operation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Open Protocols</h2>
      <p>
        Our systems are built on open communication standards including MODBUS, BACnet, and other industry protocols. This means they integrate with existing building management systems and aren't locked to a single vendor.
      </p>

